AUD:E_0117{date:"2026-07-19T01:07:54Z", event:"E-0117", task:"T-005", kind:"task_complete", agent:"alfred", result:"G-9 root cause: cortex package absent => core/state/__init__.py try/except ImportError did NOT define _cc_* names, so submodule top-level 'from . import _cc_*' raised ImportError (circular). Fix: in __init__.py except branch, define _cc_ast/_cc_lexer/_cc_parser/_cc_validator/_cc_writer/_cc_mutations/_cc_selectors/_cc_transactions/_cc_renderer = None. Now 'from . import _cc_*' succeeds (returns None) and requires_codec_cortex() gates usage at runtime. Validation: pyenv 3.11 (no cortex) 'import arqux.pulse' OK; tool py3.12 (cortex) pytest 830 passed / 34 failed. The 34 remaining failures are pre-existing CORTEX template validation errors (E017/E033) in repo .cortex files, unrelated to G-9.", evidence:"G-9 root cause: cortex package absent => core/state/__init__.py try/except ImportError did NOT define _cc_* names, so submodule top-level 'from . import _cc_*' raised ImportError (circular). Fix: in __init__.py except branch, define _cc_ast/_cc_lexer/_cc_parser/_cc_validator/_cc_writer/_cc_mutations/_cc_selectors/_cc_transactions/_cc_renderer = None. Now 'from . import _cc_*' succeeds (returns None) and requires_codec_cortex() gates usage at runtime. Validation: pyenv 3.11 (no cortex) 'import arqux.pulse' OK; tool py3.12 (cortex) pytest 830 passed / 34 failed. The 34 remaining failures are pre-existing CORTEX template validation errors (E017/E033) in repo .cortex files, unrelated to G-9.", cycle:"CYCLE-07"}
