AUD:E_0124{date:"2026-07-19T01:30:46Z", event:"E-0124", task:"T-006", kind:"task_complete", agent:"alfred", result:"G-12 root cause: _build_task_doc wrapped parsed body content into attrs dicts ({\"text\": content}, {\"criterion\": content}, etc.) WITHOUT stripping an already-serialized prefix. On re-write of a corrupted/already-serialized .cortex, content already carried 'text=' / 'criterion=' prefixes, so write_cortex rendered text:\"text=...\" -> duplicated prefix each round-trip (confirmed via repro: 'text=- text=- text=Corregir' and 'criterion=criterion=AC-1'). Fix: added _strip_attr_prefix(value, key) in formats.py that removes any leading run of '<key>=' and/or bullet markers ('- ', '* ') using regex, applied to OBJ/STP/CNST/CLAIM/BLK/NOTE/EVIDENCE entries. Also normalized OBJ to per-line bullet/prefix stripping like the other sections. Added tests/test_writer_roundtrip.py (3 tests: clean roundtrip, corrupted idempotent heal, repeated prefix collapse) — all pass. Full suite: 833 passed / 34 failed; the 34 failures are pre-existing CORTEX template validation errors (E017/E033) unrelated to G-12.", evidence:"G-12 root cause: _build_task_doc wrapped parsed body content into attrs dicts ({\"text\": content}, {\"criterion\": content}, etc.) WITHOUT stripping an already-serialized prefix. On re-write of a corrupted/already-serialized .cortex, content already carried 'text=' / 'criterion=' prefixes, so write_cortex rendered text:\"text=...\" -> duplicated prefix each round-trip (confirmed via repro: 'text=- text=- text=Corregir' and 'criterion=criterion=AC-1'). Fix: added _strip_attr_prefix(value, key) in formats.py that removes any leading run of '<key>=' and/or bullet markers ('- ', '* ') using regex, applied to OBJ/STP/CNST/CLAIM/BLK/NOTE/EVIDENCE entries. Also normalized OBJ to per-line bullet/prefix stripping like the other sections. Added tests/test_writer_roundtrip.py (3 tests: clean roundtrip, corrupted idempotent heal, repeated prefix collapse) — all pass. Full suite: 833 passed / 34 failed; the 34 failures are pre-existing CORTEX template validation errors (E017/E033) unrelated to G-12.", cycle:"CYCLE-07"}
